Two loves I have, of comfort and despair,
That like two spirits do suggest me still.
My better angel is a man right fair,
With his short gentle breast adorned with jewels,
Nor bears a beard, nor saiseth in a shade;
Nor can I in what I love be pleasing,
Or in those who do my love's fairest love.
  You still love what my sweet love bestows,
  But are these from you as is to all others;
  In my affections do I make love more,
  And yet, 'tis not the likeness of me to you,
  For love is only what I have.
   My love is your own light, your love as your shadow.
 


